text.section:
The Baltimore City Juvenile Justice Center shall include:
the Department;
the Juvenile Division of the Circuit Court for Baltimore City;
an office of the State's Attorney for Baltimore City;
an office of the Baltimore City Department of Social Services;
Baltimore City police services; and
courthouse security services of the Sheriff of Baltimore City.

If a child who is delinquent or is alleged to have committed a delinquent act is taken into custody by a law enforcement officer and brought to the Baltimore City Juvenile Justice Center, the Department, in conjunction with Baltimore City police services, shall:
for purposes of positive identification, obtain photographs and fingerprints and submit them to:
the Criminal Justice Information System Central Repository; and
any other automated juvenile justice information system or repository approved by the Secretary;
conduct a criminal and juvenile history records check; and
conduct an automated search for outstanding warrants and writs of attachment.
